area_name: Sit There and Take it Like a Man

climbs.name: She Didn't Want Me To Do It

content.description:
Not sure if anyone gets on this one these days, but it's damn fun. Big pulls on pockets under the roof and then a crux getting over the lip. Unique in that when you start you're about 6 feet off the ground, in the middle you're 8 feet off the ground and when you finish you're about 2 feet off the ground. The 3rd edition of Rick's

She Made/Had/Didn't...

series, although I don't think he actually named this one, pretty sure I did it for him. Good fun.
content.protection: Pad, 2 good spotters in the cave.
content.location:
When the main trail spits you out on the slabs,

She Didn't Want Me To Do It

is a decent sized boulder that straddles a small chasm. Jump into the cave and start as far back as you can on a couple good holds.

content.description: Sit start on jugs in the cave, move up into the pocket, match, and throw for the top.
content.location: Follow the shelf above King Dinosaur south for about 30 feet and you should see the horizontal protruding boulder.  Stay to the left of the brush and wrap back around to get to the boulder.

content.description:
This is more of a problem to goof around on if your bored in the area. Â If you're looking for a more serious problem, princess coco is way better and more fun.

Start on obvious lower lip, shoot up to the upper lip and the rest is a cakewalk.

Probably a V1 if you campus it which is what made it more fun for me.
